HEADWORD: nuclear energy
<hw>nuclear energy</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Energy derived from nuclear
reactions; -- used at present especially of electrical power generated
in atomic reactors, but encompassing also fusion energy.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> atomic energy, atomic power, nuclear energy, nuclear
power.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

